name: city-limits-2004-east-baton-rouge-parish-louisiana
notes: This is a graphical polygon dataset depicting the polygon boundaries of the incorporated city limits of Baton Rouge, Baker, and Zachary within East Baton Rouge Parish, Louisiana. The incorporated city of Baton Rouge covers an area of approximately 74.4 square miles (2004) and has an approximate population of 230,000 (2000 Census). The incorporated city of Baker covers approximately 7.9 square miles (2004) with a population of 13,793 (2000 Census). The incorporated city of Zachary covers an area of approximately 23.7 square miles (2004) with a population of 11,275 (2000 Census). The availability of public services and the application of a wide array of taxes will depend on whether or not a property is located within city limits. This dataset conveys the best currently (2004) available representation of the city limits of the cities of Baton Rouge, Baker and Zachary, Louisiana.
